\pard\f0\fs28 ({\b 17-20}).{\b  P. aviculare} group. Annuals. Stems erect, ascending or procumbent, 10-60 cm. Leaves variable in shape and size, entire, acute to obtuse, green or somewhat glaucous. Ochreae silvery-hyaline, often brownish near the base, with few, faint veins, lacerate. Flowers solitary or in axillary clusters of 2-6; bracts leaflike. Perianth-segments greenish with white, pink or reddish margins. Nut 1·5-4 mm, punctulate, dull, included in or slightly exserted from the perianth.
