\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. P. acetosum} Bieb.,{\i  Fl. Taur.-Cauc. }{\b 1:} 304 (1808). Annual. Stems procumbent or ascending, branched; sap with acid taste. Ochreae silvery-hyaline, with very faint veins. Leaves 2-3 cm, linear-oblong, obtuse, rarely acute, somewhat fleshy, veinless, covered with minute, white tubercles and appearing glaucous. Flowers in clusters of 3-7. Perianth bluish-green; segments with white margins. Nut 1·7-3 mm, slightly glossy. {\i W. Kazakhstan; S.E. Russia}. Rs(E). ({\i S.W. Asia.})
