\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. PERSICARIA (Miller) DC. Herbs. Ochreae usually brownish, entire or ciliate but not lacerate. Flowers in spikes; bracts few and inconspicuous. Perianth usually petaloid; stamens 5-8; styles 2, rarely 3, united below. Nut lenticular or trigonous. (Incl. Sect.{\i  Cephalophilon} Meissner,{\i  Echinocaulon} Meissner.)
