\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 23. P. minus} Hudson,{\i  Fl. Angl.} 148 (1762). Glabrous annual. Stems 10-40 cm, slender, decumbent or ascending, more rarely erect. Ochreae with long cilia. Leaves 25-75 × 3-9 mm, usually 6-9 times as long as wide, narrowly oblong-lanceolate, subsessile. Spikes slender, lax, often interrupted below, erect. Perianth 2-2·5 mm, deep pink (rarely white). Nut 1·8-2·5 mm, black, glossy. 2n = 40. {\i Wet places. From N. Spain and Macedonia northwards to} 67°{\i  N.in Russia.} Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs(N, B, C, W, K, E) Su [Lu].
